http://www.dl3e.com/corerules/display.cfm?id=47</font></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ujaaxtherogue.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jaax the Rogue</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/6/02 4:14:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2050.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Crossbows</span><hr size=1> I actually really enjoy pulling.. IF I have a tank or two with me, that can get aggro when I get back. <br>
Then, I use my crossbow quite a lot. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Never in RvR. Never when soloing.<br>
<br>
Jaax. <p><img src="http://www.flavonsen.com/images/jaax-new2.jpg">
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ugalium.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Galium</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/6/02 4:29:53 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2050.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Crossbows</span><hr size=1> I use mine a fair bit for a variety of different uses:<br>
<br>
Pulling - probably the biggest use. Mostly this comes into play when you want to speed pull. If I pull the casters can sit and regain mana, fighters can regain endurance and I keep the mobs coming. Also lots of times depending on the group makeup I am the only one suitable for pulling. Our low damage xbow shot rarely builds enough aggro for anyont to worry about.<br>
<br>
RvR - limited only by your imagination, well that and its crappy damage. The other day I actually killed a green con troll with my xbow when he was bashing on the keep doors, guess he didnt notice me slowly wittle down his HP <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Normally however I use it in the front lines of a fight. Sometimes some caster will be the one holding back the troops with mez or some AoE whenever someone tries to get close. Funny how creeping up and putting a bolt into him, even our pathetic damage bolts, will cause them to turn and run, thus opening up the doors for the rest of our troops. Obviously perforating their arteries would be better, but sometimes thats not an option.<br>
<br>
So in short, not a huge power tool, but does have its uses from time to time. Indepsensible in soloing, great for pulling mobs out to you.<br>
<br>
<br>
Culdor<br>
<br>
